  "@id": "ocp:sep/structural-realism",
  "meta": {
    "title": "Structural Realism",
    "description": "Structural realism is considered by many realists and antirealists alike as the most defensible form of scientific realism. There are different forms of structural realism, and an extensive literature about their pros and cons, and how they relate to case studies from science and its history. There are connections with debates in metaphysics, philosophical logic and philosophy of mathematics. This entry is a comprehensive survey of the field.",
